quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  24,1,"[This is] a surah which We have sent down and prescribed, and We have sent down in it manifest signs so that you may take admonition"
  24,2,"As for the fornicatress and the fornicator, strike each of them a hundred lashes, and let not pity for them overcome you in Allah’s law, if you believe in Allah and the Last Day, and let their punishment be witnessed by a group of the faithful"
  24,3,"The fornicator will not marry anyone but a fornicatress or an idolatress, and the fornicatress will be married by none except a fornicator or an idolater, and that is forbidden to the faithful"
  24,4,"As for those who accuse chaste women and do not bring four witnesses, strike them eighty lashes, and never accept any testimony from them after that, and they are transgressors"
  24,5,"excepting those who repent after that and reform, for Allah is indeed all-forgiving, all-merciful"
  24,6,"As for those who accuse their wives [of adultery], but have no witnesses except themselves, the testimony of such a man shall be a fourfold testimony [sworn] by Allah that he is indeed stating the truth"
  24,7,"and a fifth [oath] that Allah’s wrath shall be upon him if he were lying"
  24,8,"The punishment shall be averted from her by her testifying with four oaths [sworn] by Allah that he is indeed lying"
  24,9,"and a fifth [oath] that Allah’s wrath shall be upon her if he were stating the truth"
  24,10,"Were it not for Allah’s grace and His mercy upon you, and that Allah is all-clement, all-wise"
  24,11,"Indeed those who initiated the calumny are a group from among yourselves. Do not suppose it is bad thing for you. No, it is for your good. Each man among them bears [the onus for] his share in the sin, and as for him who assumed its major burden from among them, there is a great punishment for him"
  24,12,"When you [first] heard about it, why did not the faithful, men and women, think well of their folks, and say, ‘This is an obvious calumny’"
  24,13,"Why did they not bring four witnesses to it? So when they could not bring the witnesses, they are liars in Allah’s sight"
  24,14,"Were it not for Allah’s grace and His mercy upon you in this world and the Hereafter, there would have befallen you a great punishment for what you ventured into"
  24,15,"when you were receiving it on your tongues, and were mouthing something of which you had no knowledge, supposing it to be a light matter, while it was a grave [matter] with Allah"
  24,16,"And why did you not, when you heard it, say, ‘It is not for us to say such a thing. [O Allah!] You are immaculate! This is a monstrous calumny!’"
  24,17,"Allah advises you lest you should ever repeat the like of it, should you be faithful"
  24,18,"Allah clarifies the signs for you, and Allah is all-knowing, all-wise"
  24,19,"Indeed those who want indecency to spread among the faithful—there is a painful punishment for them in the world and the Hereafter, and Allah knows and you do not know"
  24,20,"Were it not for Allah’s grace and His mercy upon you, and that Allah is all-kind, all-merciful…"